==Introduction==
A Concepts can '''inherit''' from another Concepts, creating even complex '''Parent -> Child Concepts inheritance hierarchy'''.

All data entities of Children Concepts are considered to belong also to all Parent Concepts categories.

The Children Concept DON'T formally inherit/use the Properties of its Parents.
However, it is '''recommended''' that:
* Parent Concept shall define a set of Properties common for all its Children Concepts
* Children Concepts shall reuse as much as possible the Parents Properties (in optimal case all Parent Properties)
* Children Concept can add its own specific Properties

If the Parent Concept is abstract, which means no capability to add instances of that Concept, it should be marked as type="Virtual".


==Definition==
<pre>
<concept name="{PARENT CONCEPT}" ... type="Virtual">
  <property name="{COMMON PROPERTY 1}">
  <property name="{COMMON PROPERTY 2}">
  <property name="{COMMON PROPERTY 3}">
</concept>

<concept name="{CHILD CONCEPT}" ... parent="{PARENT CONCEPT}">              <!-- reused ALL Parent Properties -->
  <property name="{COMMON PROPERTY 1}">
  <property name="{COMMON PROPERTY 2}">
  <property name="{COMMON PROPERTY 3}">
  <property name="{SPECIFIC PROPERTY 1}">
  <property name="{SPECIFIC PROPERTY 2}">
</concept>

<concept name="{GRAND CHILD CONCEPT}" ... parent="{CHILD CONCEPT}">
  <property name="{COMMON PROPERTY1}">               <!-- reused property from Grand Parent -->
  <property name="{SPECIFIC PROPERTY 1}">            <!-- reused property from Parent -->
  <property name="{SPECIFIC PROPERTY A}">
  <property name="{SPECIFIC PROPERTY B}">
</concept>
</pre>

{| class="helptable"
|-
! Virtual
| Mark abstract Parent classes with type="Virtual"
|-
! {PARENT CONCEPT}
| A short name of the '''Parent''' Concept.
|-
! {CHILD CONCEPT}
| A name of the '''Child''' Concept which inherits from the {PARENT CONCEPT}
|-
! {COMMON PROPERTY}
| A name of the common Property defined in the Parent Concept and re-used in by the Children Concepts
|-
! {SPECIFIC PROPERTY}
| A name of the specific Property defined only in specific Children Concept
|}


==Semantic database==
Children Concepts are defined as a sub-categories of the Parent Concept.

All queries to the Parent Concept will return also data entities from all Children Concepts (including Category Pages).


==Example==
<pre>
<concept name="Car">                         <!-- Parent Concept -->
  <structure>
    <property name="Made by"/>
    <property name="Model"/>
    <property name="Engine"/>
    <property name="Color"/>
  </structure>
</concept>

<concept name="Truck" parent="Car">          <!-- Child Concept -->
  <structure>
    <property name="Made by"/>
    <property name="Model"/>
    <property name="Engine"/>
    <property name="Color"/>

    <property name="Tonnage"/>
  </structure>

  <concept name="Bus" parent="Car">           <!-- Child Concept -->
    <structure>
      <property name="Made by"/>
      <property name="Model"/>
      <property name="Engine"/>
      <property name="Color"/>

      <property name="Doors"/>
    </structure>
</concept>
</pre>


==User Interface==
The Cars Category Page will display all Cars: Trucks and Buses.
